Rating: 3
No need for TWO cups of sugar and no need for liners! I adjusted this recipe according to suggestions by one reviewer (from the Carribean, 8/21/03) and used a lot less sugar (1/2 cup brown & 1/2 cup white) and used a mix of all purp & whole wheat flour. I crushed the cereal before measuring. I added a tsp. of baking powder since others commented on the lack of rise, but I don't think that did much since they were still somewhat short! I baked using the convection feature on my oven (at 375) and they were beautifully golden in half the time and they popped EASILY out of the pan since I used cooking spray. Anyway, they were perfectly delicious and the cream cheese filling added a nice touch - worth the extra step! Now, if I can oly figure out how to make them gluten free...

