Rating: 3
I halved the recipe; used 1 cup all purpose and 1/4 cup wheat flour. 1/2 cup brown sugar, 1/4 cup white sugar. Added chopped dried apricots (instead of raisins). Came out pretty well. Baked at 375 for 25 minutes. Fast, easy, popped right out of muffin tins (greased with butter). A little chewy on the bottoms. Served warm with strawberry rhubarb jam. Will make these again.

