Rating: 4
I took the suggestion of 1/2 c of sugar & honey each but added about 1 cup more flour, used an organic whole grain cereal (Optimum Zen) & reduced the oven temp to 375. The type of sugar I use is Rapadura, which is as natural as you can get, so I'm sure that made a huge difference in the flavor & sweetness. I'm not a muffin person but these are very good. If you don't like how they come out, you did something wrong.

Rating: 3
I have made this recipe many times and it is always a hit. More often than not, I omit the cream cheese filling and add 2 cups of blueberries. I also make them with fresh cranberries. Delicious.

Rating: 4
This recipe has got a bad rap and with a couple of simple adjustments is the best bran muffin in my repetoire. Instead of 2 cups sugar, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup honey is more than enough sweetness and 1 and 1/2 cup whole wheat flour and one cup white instead of all white. I bake them at 375 instead of 4 and I normally get 18/20 muffins because I often bake them without the filling. Fill the tins almost full because it is true, these muffins don't rise a lot but they are moist and delicious and I have never had somebody tell me that they don't like them and I have made them for years. Whew, long sentence. Just spray your tin with cooking spray and they will pop out, no need to use paper cups. Hope this helps.

Rating: 3
I just made these muffins yesterday and made a ton of changes but received great reviews. I picked this recipe because I was looking for something more dense than just a cakey muffin. Yes, they are alittle difficult to release from the pans...but well worth the effort. As for the sweetness of the recipe..If you like sweet you will love this. I was looking for a bran recipe to add fresh blueberries to, so I added about 1 1/2 cups fresh blueberries. I cut back the sugar to 1 3/4 cup. Replaced 1 cup white flour with whole wheat flour and added about 1/2 cup oats. I did do the suprise middle on half and my husband who hates cream cheese still loved them. I did not have any problems with them rising as some others have suggested. To my suprise I loved the raisin bran! I would love to try this recipe again with fresh raspberries.

